HEADWORD: Aurilave
<hw>Au`ri*lave</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>auris</ets> ear + <ets>lavare</ets> to wash.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for cleansing the ear, consisting of a small piece of sponge
on an ivory or bone handle.</def>⟦br⟧
